called the broken branch,

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:30.060
no one thinks you mean
the court system.

00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:32.370
But at the same time,
no one writes a book

00:05:32.370 --> 00:05:36.500
with that title unless they believe
that what's broken can be fixed

00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:38.790
and unless they think that
what's broken is fundamental

00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:41.440
if not primary to the system.

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:44.690 position:56%
Of course, a key challenge of
diagnosing and reforming congress is

00:05:44.690 --> 00:05:48.950
that no one really agrees on what
a functioning congress looks like.

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:52.480
For some like Wilson had
a responsible party flavor

00:05:52.480 --> 00:05:56.340 position:56%
in which a majority party can easily
enact its national program upon the

00:05:56.340 --> 00:06:00.790 position:56%
greased skids of strong leadership,
majoritarian rules and parliamentary

00:06:00.790 --> 00:06:03.480
like discipline among
the rank-and-file.

00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:05.950
For others it's largely
the opposite,

00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:08.260
a decentralized legislature

00:06:08.260 --> 00:06:11.230
with strong committees
bolting a policy expertise

00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:14.200
that can thoughtfully craft
durable and successful policy

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:18.160 position:56%
and multiple [inaudible] points that
require the meaningful participation

00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:21.480
and deliberation of all
members, including the minority.

00:06:21.480 --> 00:06:23.960
Still others don't even think
about it in this dimension

00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:26.110
and when they think about
congressional form they're looking

00:06:26.110 --> 00:06:29.480
to seek or increase the relative
power of congress outside

00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:32.840
